    "# 26. The Gate Automation & Damage Detection Problem\n",
    "\n",
    "## Tier 1: The Pen & Paper Method (Mathematical Formulation)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Goal\n",
    "Formulate the gate automation and damage detection problem as a mixed-integer programming model that simultaneously optimizes sensor monitoring, maintenance scheduling, and failure prediction.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key assumptions\n",
    "- Multiple gates with different sensor types (photo-eye, ground loop, safety beam)\n",
    "- Sensors can fail with different probabilities based on monitoring status\n",
    "- Gate downtime costs are significantly higher than monitoring costs\n",
    "- Maintenance can restore sensor health but requires scheduling\n",
    "- Demand patterns vary by time of day and gate location\n",
    "\n",
    "### Approach (step-by-step)\n",
    "1. Define sets for gates, sensors, time periods, and failure modes\n",
    "2. Establish parameters for costs, failure rates, and demand\n",
    "3. Create decision variables for monitoring, failures, and operational status\n",
    "4. Formulate objective function to minimize total cost\n",
    "5. Add constraints for monitoring requirements, failure detection, and sensor health\n",
    "6. Solve using mixed-integer programming with fallback enumeration\n",
    "\n",
    "### What to look for in the results\n",
    "- Optimal monitoring schedule that balances cost and reliability\n",
    "- Sensor health degradation patterns over time\n",
    "- Trade-offs between monitoring investment and downtime prevention\n",
    "- Impact of demand variations on resource allocation\n",
    "\n",
    "### Concrete example (from the source)\n",
    "A facility with 2 gates, each equipped with 3 sensor types over a 24-hour period.\n",
    "- Gate 1 handles 150 vehicles/hour during peak periods\n",
    "- Gate 2 handles 100 vehicles/hour\n",
    "- Monitoring costs: $5 per sensor per hour\n",
    "- Downtime costs: $15,000/hour (Gate 1), $10,000/hour (Gate 2)\n",
    "- Failure rates: 0.02 for all sensors"
   ]
  },
