    "### Why this Tier exists vs earlier Tiers\n",
    "This is Tier 1, the foundational mathematical approach. It provides:\n",
    "- **Optimal solutions** with provable optimality guarantees\n",
    "- **Complete problem formulation** capturing all constraints and objectives\n",
    "- **Baseline performance** for comparing heuristic and advanced methods\n",
    "- **Theoretical foundation** for understanding the problem structure\n",
    "\n",
    "### Pros / Cons vs other approaches\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pros:**\n",
    "- Guarantees optimal solution (when solvable)\n",
    "- Comprehensive modeling of all problem aspects\n",
    "- Provides benchmark for other methods\n",
    "- Handles complex constraints systematically\n",
    "\n",
    "**Cons:**\n",
    "- Computationally intensive for large instances\n",
    "- May not scale to real-time decision making\n",
    "- Requires precise parameter estimates\n",
    "- Limited flexibility for dynamic changes\n",
    "\n",
    "### When to use this Tier\n",
    "- **Strategic planning** where optimality is critical\n",
    "- **Small to medium instances** with limited gates and time periods\n",
    "- **Benchmark studies** to evaluate other methods\n",
    "- **Design phase** to understand problem characteristics\n",
    "- **Academic research** requiring theoretical foundations\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Insights from the Mathematical Formulation\n",
    "\n",
    "The optimization results demonstrate several important insights:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Cost-Benefit Balance**: The optimal solution shows that investing in comprehensive monitoring (high utilization) significantly reduces costly downtime, justifying the monitoring expenses.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Critical Sensor Prioritization**: The mathematical model automatically identifies which sensors deserve continuous monitoring based on their impact on gate availability and overall system cost.\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **System-Wide Optimization**: Unlike greedy approaches, the MIP considers the entire 24-hour horizon simultaneously, leading to better long-term strategies rather than myopic decisions.\n",
    "\n",
    "4. **Resource Allocation Efficiency**: The budget constraints force the optimizer to make intelligent trade-offs, ensuring monitoring resources are deployed where they provide the highest return on investment.\n",
    "\n",
    "This mathematical foundation provides the optimal benchmark against which all subsequent tiers (heuristics, metaheuristics, machine learning) will be compared."
